 ways his business applies concepts and principles that cadets are currently learning in their Marketing  Operations Management  and Statistics courses  Mr  Adams also coordinated interviews for Cadets seeking full time employment and summer internships in supply chain management  Two rising first class cadets will be working as interns at Intelitap this summer  Additionally  Sigma Beta Delta organized a panel of alumni from the Darden School of Business at the University of Virginia to give Cadets a better perspective on the application process and the benefits of graduate school in the current job market  Participants included Joseph Pederson  03  Ryan Peay  02  and Rob McLean  03 who are currently enrolled at Darden as well as Reggie Webb  75 from the Darden Administration Office and Vincent LaPietra  03 who is enrolled in the JAG program at UVA  ODE continues to produce the ECBU Online Journal which presents a sampling of the student writing  New this year was the Best Paper award given to Cadet Christopher Martin for his paper  An Economic Superpower  Trade and Pollution in China  Further  ODE held weekly meetings to discuss the political economic issues of the day  Spring 2010 Newsletter AACSB Accreditation  Field Test  Faculty Research  Lopez Chair  Experiential Learning  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  FED Reserve Field Trip  SBD   ODE Activity  Beta Gamma Sigma  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey  Stay Connected  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Informat